<?xml version="1.0" encoding="utf-8"?>  <legaldoc><law type="statute"><section><amendatorysection chaptername="Revenue And Taxation" statutenumber="77-204"><bookinfo>Reissue Revised Statutes of Nebraska</bookinfo><statuteno>77-204</statuteno><catchline>Real estate taxes; when delinquent.</catchline><para>One-half of the taxes due under section 77-203 shall become delinquent on May 1 and the second half on September 1 next following the date the taxes become due, except that in counties having a population of more than one hundred thousand, the first half shall become delinquent April 1 and the second half August 1 next following the date the taxes become due.</para></amendatorysection></section><source><para>Laws 1903, c. 73, &#167; 150, p. 442; </para><para>R.S.1913, &#167; 6479; </para><para>C.S.1922, &#167; 6002; </para><para>Laws 1925, c. 43, &#167; 10, p. 172; </para><para>C.S.1929, &#167; 77-1907; </para><para>Laws 1933, c. 134, &#167; 1, p. 513; </para><para>Laws 1935, c. 151, &#167; 1, p. 557; </para><para>Laws 1937, c. 167, &#167; 2, p. 636; </para><para>Laws 1939, c. 98, &#167; 2, p. 421; </para><para>Laws 1941, c. 157, &#167; 2, p. 607; </para><para>C.S.Supp.,1941, &#167; 77-1959; </para><para>R.S.1943, &#167; 77-204; </para><para>Laws 1961, c. 373, &#167; 1, p. 1148; </para><para>Laws 1965, c. 471, &#167; 1, p. 1518; </para><para>Laws 1967, c. 497, &#167; 1, p. 1689; </para><para>Laws 1987, LB 508, &#167; 4. </para></source></law></legaldoc> 